<p>We have a server that converts audio to text.</p>  <p><strong><em>Audio to Text:</em></strong></p>  <p><strong>Post service url</strong>: <a href="http://ivos.kz/api" rel="nofollow">http://ivos.kz/api</a></p>  <p>Post request parameters:</p>  <p><strong>uuid:</strong> given uuid</p>  <p><strong>apikey:</strong> given apikey</p>  <p><strong>type:</strong> text | query | orders | address | dates | names | numbers | music</p>  <p><strong>format:</strong> wav</p>  <p><strong>media:</strong> wav file</p>  <p><strong>My code:</strong></p>  <pre><code>import requests import json  url = "http://ivos.kz/api" audiofile = './asd.wav'  with open(audiofile, 'rb') as f:     r = requests.post(url, header = {'Content-Type': 'audio/wav'}, data = {'uuid': &lt;my uuid&gt;, 'apikey': &lt;my api key&gt;, 'type': 'text', 'format': 'wav', 'media': f.read()})     with open("asd.html", "w") as ff:         ff.write(r.text.encode('utf-8').strip()) </code></pre>  <p>I am getting response: "empty post", and if I send this request without headers I am getting response: "Unsupported media"</p>  <p>Any suggestions? </p>